INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('378', '1', '2015-05-08 12:45:16', '2015-05-08 12:45:16', '<h2 class=\"font_8\">Business and Property Owners</h2>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\">PACE enables property owners to obtain low-cost, long-term loans for up to 100% of all costs associated with the design and installation of water conservation, energy efficiency, renewable and distributed generation retrofits. These improvements can be structured to generate positive cash flow to the property owner because the cost savings derived from them exceeds the amount of the PACE assessment payment. In addition, PACE enables the property owner to amortize the cost of the improvements over their useful life. Inasmuch as PACE loans are secured by assessments on the property, they are automatically transferred to successive owners when the property is sold. Consequently, each owner of the property pays only that portion of the assessment that accrues during its period of ownership. And importantly for property owners leasing their property to tenants, PACE assessments can be passed to tenants under the typical commercial office lease.</p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\">These attributes of PACE loans enable property owners to overcome traditional barriers to making capital investments in property. Without PACE, property owners will continue tossing the problem of delayed maintenance on their property’s aging physical plant to a new owner like a hot potato. Until committing capital to modernize real property infrastructure makes sense as a value proposition, property owners will continue to waste operating expenditures on utility bills and risk exposure to utility price increases. Instead, PACE users capitalize money previously spent on utilities; the utility cost savings achieved by a retrofit pay for the retrofit itself. Property owners end up with more valuable property and access to recurring utility savings and pay only for the assessments that accrue while they own the property.</p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\">The  Texas PACE Authority has partnered with the US Green Building Council in providing a list of PACE Service Providers, which may be found by clicking here:</p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><a href=\"http://texasgreenbuildingmarketplace.org/listing/guide/pace-related\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-171 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Texas_GreenBuilding_Marketplace_440-300x169.png\" alt=\"Texas Green Building Marketplace Logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a></p>\r\n<p class=\"font_8\"><em>DISCLAIMER: Texas PACE Authority neither endorses nor recommends any particular service providers, including those found in the USGBC Directory. If you are a service provider and would like to be included in this directory, please contact USGBC.</em></p>', 'For Property Owners', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-08 12:45:16', '2015-05-08 12:45:16', '', '6', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/?p=378', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('380', '1', '2015-05-08 12:49:10', '2015-05-08 12:49:10', '<h1>Who We Are</h1>\r\nThe Texas PACE Authority was founded as a nonprofit organization in 2015 with the express goal of streamlining the implementation of PACE-funded clean energy projects in Texas using the \"PACE in a Box\" model. The statute authorizing PACE in Texas (SB 385) was passed by the Texas Legislature in 2013 and The Texas PACE Authority is now expanding to counties and municipalities across Texas.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2> Staff</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-114\" src=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/charlene-300x278.jpg\" alt=\"Picture of Charlene\" width=\"150\" height=\"139\" />\r\n<h3>Charlene Heydinger</h3>\r\nCharlene Heydinger also serves as the executive director of Keeping PACE in Texas, the trade association created in 2012 to promote Property Assessed Clean Energy (PACE) financing in Texas. Ms. Heydinger is a public affairs strategist.\r\n\r\nCharlene worked on Capital Hill for over nine years and then as vice president and Washington counsel for ABC, Inc. She also served as executive director of the Morton and Angela Topfer Family Foundation. Ms. Heydinger is a member of the Texas, Washington, DC, and Michigan Bar Associations.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:charlene.heydinger@keeppace.org\">charlene.heydinger@keeppace.org</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-116\" src=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/jonathan-300x278.jpg\" alt=\"picture of jonathon blackburn\" width=\"150\" height=\"139\" />\r\n<h3>Jonathon Blackburn</h3>\r\n<p class=\"font_7\">Prior to moving to Austin, Jonathon lived in the UK and worked for a venture and commercialization firm developing technology startups. He co-founded a University of Cambridge spin-out that is building a mobile clean energy storage system.  Jonathon started his career as an engineer at the electric utility Southern Company in environmental and energy policy, before moving to its wholesale division developing some of Southern’s first forays into utility-scale renewable energy power plants.</p>\r\n<p class=\"font_7\">Jonathon holds graduate degrees from the University of Cambridge and Duke University. He also has a BS in Chemical Engineering from Mississippi State University.</p>\r\n<p class=\"font_7\"><a href=\"mailto:jonathon.blackburn@texaspaceauthority.org\">jonathon.blackburn@texaspaceauthority.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/joe.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-115\" src=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/joe.jpg\" alt=\"joe\" width=\"150\" height=\"139\" /></a>Joe Edgar</h3>\r\nJoe leverages his extensive experience in startup businesses and real estate finance to evaluate PACE project applications.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Joe managed the J4T Venture Fund, a $46.5M fund focused on Texas early-stage companies. He is a member of the U.S. Treasury SSBCI Venture Capital Steering Committee, which aims to share best practices across state lines in regards to venture capital and entrepreneurial ecosystems.\r\n\r\nPrior to managing the J4T Venture Fund Joe was with Texas Governor Perry’s office and managed over $450M in state authority with a focus on early-stage Texas companies. Before joining the governor’s office, he was the Managing Partner of E.I. Investments a $10M fund focused on early-stage investment in Oregon and Texas.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>PACE in a Box</h1>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">To expedite the establishment of local PACE programs in Texas and to facilitate a consistent, state-wide approach to PACE design and implementation, Keeping PACE in <span class=\"s1\">Texas, </span> a nonprofit non-partisan association, organized a broad-based coalition of more than 130 stakeholders to develop a free toolkit for local governments to use in creating and implementing their PACE programs.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.keepingpaceintexas.org/pace-in-a-box/\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-101 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/PACEinaBox-logo-150x150.png\" alt=\"PACE In A Box\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">The toolkit, known as <em>\"PACE in a Box,\"</em> contains all of the design elements, documents, and implementation steps necessary for a local government to establish an effective PACE program quickly and economically. <em>PACE in a Box </em> is the first and only PACE program designed by market stakeholders. The open-market model creates a uniform, user-friendly, sustainable and scalable PACE program for Texas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Find PACE in a Box at <a href=\"http://www.keepingpaceintexas.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.KeepingPACEinTexas.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"p1\">Start Saving Energy, Water and Money Now</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For more information about adopting a PACE program in your region, taking advantage of the program, or volunteering to educate municipalities and other stakeholders, visit the website:</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><a href=\"http://www.keepingpaceintexas.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.KeepingPACEinTexas.org</a></p>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '113-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-08 12:49:10', '2015-05-08 12:49:10', '', '113', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/?p=380', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('601', '1', '2015-09-13 16:47:30', '2015-09-13 16:47:30', '<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-968\" src=\"http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/wp-content/uploads/HPB2016_outline-204x300.jpg\" alt=\"HPB2016_outline\" width=\"204\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nOur signature events are a series of contractor training workshops. These half-day workshops will answer all your in-depth questions about PACE. Join us at our next workshop as we partner with the High Performance Buildings Conference in Austin on May 2nd! Register at:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nfmt.com/highperformance/education/sessiondetails.aspx?id=2656\">Austin Contractor Training</a>\r\n\r\nHope to see you there!\r\n\r\nFor questions, contact admin@texaspaceauthority.org\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit: \"<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/usacehq/5056771149/in/photolist-8GRgTt-9GzLgu-9A9WT9-9HEdHK-ayZJhh-9VTAzN-apamtg-7VdRWo-9XJcec-9Gx3AT-ewVayZ-aoWWxA-ayX5D6-m8rF6Y-bXPwWL-ewXUuL-bXPx77-8CEaDU-cha7yy-965NsL-7z7a5z-bXMMao-eY8dHe-jF3yxs-9GzRxj-9qPXJ4-9Jz6Q4-ekEBbH-bmvbff-bXN29U-8Vx5ze-8VA7Ab-8Vx5ba-9Jzkxp-qwVfMm-bXMr8S-bXMqHC-6EqX5C-bXMqeY-bXMJ3G-bXMr6b-9ZRAEU-8PjmEZ-9GzUb5-fK1pzx-artr2f-chawmU-cEEZW7-ciLpz7-fxRofL\">Contractors Review Plans</a>\" by <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/usacehq/\">U.S. Army Corps of Engineers</a> is licensed under <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/\">CC BY 2.0</a>', 'Join Us for Our Next Contractor Training Workshop!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'join-us-for-our-pace-contractor-training', '', '', '2016-04-01 12:58:08', '2016-04-01 12:58:08', '', '0', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/?p=601', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('912', '1', '2016-02-18 21:02:35', '2016-02-18 21:02:35', 'Our first Houston PACE Contractor Training Workshop is now full. Don\'t despair, we plan on having more workshops in the future. In the meantime, join us that night for networking at the newly opened Torchy\'s Tacos in the Woodlands. Please sign up at:\r\n\r\nhttps://www.eventbrite.com/myevent?eid=20793595203\r\n\r\nHope to see you there!\r\n\r\n\r\nFor questions, contact admin@texaspaceauthority.org\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit: \"<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/usacehq/5056771149/in/photolist-8GRgTt-9GzLgu-9A9WT9-9HEdHK-ayZJhh-9VTAzN-apamtg-7VdRWo-9XJcec-9Gx3AT-ewVayZ-aoWWxA-ayX5D6-m8rF6Y-bXPwWL-ewXUuL-bXPx77-8CEaDU-cha7yy-965NsL-7z7a5z-bXMMao-eY8dHe-jF3yxs-9GzRxj-9qPXJ4-9Jz6Q4-ekEBbH-bmvbff-bXN29U-8Vx5ze-8VA7Ab-8Vx5ba-9Jzkxp-qwVfMm-bXMr8S-bXMqHC-6EqX5C-bXMqeY-bXMJ3G-bXMr6b-9ZRAEU-8PjmEZ-9GzUb5-fK1pzx-artr2f-chawmU-cEEZW7-ciLpz7-fxRofL\">Contractors Review Plans</a>\" by <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/usacehq/\">U.S. Army Corps of Engineers</a> is licensed under <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/\">CC BY 2.0</a>', 'Join Us for Houston PACE Networking!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '601-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-18 21:02:35', '2016-02-18 21:02:35', '', '601', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/601-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('908', '1', '2016-02-11 20:49:47', '2016-02-11 20:49:47', 'Are you an engineer or contractor providing energy and water efficiency building technologies? Do you want to be a service provider in Texas\' PACE ecosystem?\r\n\r\nIf so, Texas PACE Authority would like to invite you to attend our PACE Training Workshop!\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this Training will be to discuss in detail how to complete a PACE project from start to finish, and how it can be helpful for you and Texas\' property owners. Topics of discussion will include:\r\n\r\n\"How to Market PACE\"\r\n\"Technical Standards for a Project\"\r\n\"The Application Process\"\r\n\"Available Commercial Rebates\"\r\n\"Financial Modeling of PACE Projects\"\r\nAttendees will receive lunch, a binder with printed materials including advocacy and application documents, and a USB drive containing all digital files. The cost of attendance is $75, and will cover the aforementioned lunch, binder, USB drive, and Training.\r\n\r\nSign up at the following link:\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/houston-pace-service-provider-training-february-25th-2016-tickets-19628194458\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/houston-pace-service-provider-training-february-25th-2016-tickets-19628194458</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor questions, contact admin@texaspaceauthority.org\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit: \"<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/usacehq/5056771149/in/photolist-8GRgTt-9GzLgu-9A9WT9-9HEdHK-ayZJhh-9VTAzN-apamtg-7VdRWo-9XJcec-9Gx3AT-ewVayZ-aoWWxA-ayX5D6-m8rF6Y-bXPwWL-ewXUuL-bXPx77-8CEaDU-cha7yy-965NsL-7z7a5z-bXMMao-eY8dHe-jF3yxs-9GzRxj-9qPXJ4-9Jz6Q4-ekEBbH-bmvbff-bXN29U-8Vx5ze-8VA7Ab-8Vx5ba-9Jzkxp-qwVfMm-bXMr8S-bXMqHC-6EqX5C-bXMqeY-bXMJ3G-bXMr6b-9ZRAEU-8PjmEZ-9GzUb5-fK1pzx-artr2f-chawmU-cEEZW7-ciLpz7-fxRofL\">Contractors Review Plans</a>\" by <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/usacehq/\">U.S. Army Corps of Engineers</a> is licensed under <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/\">CC BY 2.0</a>', 'Join Us for our Houston PACE Contractor Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '601-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 20:49:47', '2016-02-11 20:49:47', '', '601', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/601-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('602', '1', '2015-09-13 16:47:14', '2015-09-13 16:47:14', 'Are you an engineer or contractor providing energy and water efficiency building technologies? Do you want to be a service provider in Texas\' PACE ecosystem?\r\n\r\nIf so, Texas PACE Authority would like to invite you to attend our PACE Training Workshop this October 1st, from 11 AM to 4 PM at the Austin Energy Building on Barton Springs in Austin.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this Training will be to discuss in detail how to complete a PACE project from start to finish, and how it can be helpful for you and Texas\' property owners. Topics of discussion will include: \r\n\r\n\"How to Market PACE\"\r\n\"Technical Standards for a Project\"\r\n\"The Application Process\"\r\n\"Available Commercial Rebates\"\r\n\"Financial Modeling of PACE Projects\"\r\nAttendees will receive lunch, a binder with printed materials including advocacy and application documents, and a USB drive containing all digital files. The cost of attendance is $75, and will cover the aforementioned lunch, binder, USB drive, and Training. \r\n\r\nSign up at the following link (Note: Capacity for this inaugural training is limited, so be sure to sign up quickly if you would like to attend): \r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/pace-service-provider-training-october-1st-tickets-18401521446\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/pace-service-provider-training-october-1st-tickets-18401521446</a>\r\n\r\nFor questions, contact admin@texaspaceauthority.org\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit: \"<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/dawilson/6028948450/in/photolist-abKWk5-e4fzbk-afyhk9-9wBEs9-fjDNzc-5SNp9R-aovwdD-e6ivB-7qEG32-9VLrRy-feFymY-bNRbZB-fgFqTY-8zn5XP-qoWTev-7Fqi2-8NB2st-8r2H55-8NM84a-dZhLz7-f5t71P-9Zu6cQ-a9TGvJ-a9TJZS-a9TKoQ-oyex1f-dcci7Y-ncGxHU-6WvnLf-dcp22m-a9TFGu-bWcgNY-p4Qc3L-a9TGVb-a9QXXv-a9QWLZ-dgz8Tx-pVV46d-ah1ncC-g9hYY5-cBhgr1-5uAtp8-cBhg81-8xRuQv-g9npRd-bgNtuV-835yZS-EACLA-bY6b6W-6dtsES\">Blue Hour Skyline, Austin</a>\" by <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/dawilson/\">Dave Wilson</a> is licensed under <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/\">CC BY 2.0</a>', 'Join Us for our PACE Contractor Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '601-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-13 16:47:14', '2015-09-13 16:47:14', '', '601', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/601-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_bcyw_posts` VALUES('603', '1', '2015-09-13 16:50:14', '2015-09-13 16:50:14', 'Are you an engineer or contractor providing energy and water efficiency building technologies? Do you want to be a service provider in Texas\' PACE ecosystem?\r\n\r\nIf so, Texas PACE Authority would like to invite you to attend our PACE Training Workshop this October 1st, from 11 AM to 4 PM at the Austin Energy Building on Barton Springs in Austin.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this Training will be to discuss in detail how to complete a PACE project from start to finish, and how it can be helpful for you and Texas\' property owners. Topics of discussion will include: \r\n\r\n\"How to Market PACE\"\r\n\"Technical Standards for a Project\"\r\n\"The Application Process\"\r\n\"Available Commercial Rebates\"\r\n\"Financial Modeling of PACE Projects\"\r\nAttendees will receive lunch, a binder with printed materials including advocacy and application documents, and a USB drive containing all digital files. The cost of attendance is $75, and will cover the aforementioned lunch, binder, USB drive, and Training. \r\n\r\nSign up at the following link:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/pace-service-provider-training-october-1st-tickets-18401521446\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/pace-service-provider-training-october-1st-tickets-18401521446</a>\r\n\r\nFor questions, contact admin@texaspaceauthority.org\r\n\r\nPhoto Credit: \"<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/dawilson/6028948450/in/photolist-abKWk5-e4fzbk-afyhk9-9wBEs9-fjDNzc-5SNp9R-aovwdD-e6ivB-7qEG32-9VLrRy-feFymY-bNRbZB-fgFqTY-8zn5XP-qoWTev-7Fqi2-8NB2st-8r2H55-8NM84a-dZhLz7-f5t71P-9Zu6cQ-a9TGvJ-a9TJZS-a9TKoQ-oyex1f-dcci7Y-ncGxHU-6WvnLf-dcp22m-a9TFGu-bWcgNY-p4Qc3L-a9TGVb-a9QXXv-a9QWLZ-dgz8Tx-pVV46d-ah1ncC-g9hYY5-cBhgr1-5uAtp8-cBhg81-8xRuQv-g9npRd-bgNtuV-835yZS-EACLA-bY6b6W-6dtsES\">Blue Hour Skyline, Austin</a>\" by <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/dawilson/\">Dave Wilson</a> is licensed under <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/\">CC BY 2.0</a>', 'Join Us for our PACE Contractor Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '601-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-13 16:50:14', '2015-09-13 16:50:14', '', '601', 'http://www.texaspaceauthority.org/601-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
